The paper discusses the scalability and correctness of the control plane in a software-defined network (SDN), which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of SDN in service provider and data center networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
